        "rich_text_8DL9Df": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Diamonds are more than just precious stones; they’re symbols of love, commitment, and timeless beauty. But before you invest in one, knowing how to check diamond purity can help you ensure that what you’re buying is truly authentic.<br/> Whether you’re looking for a sparkling engagement ring or a<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/modern-diamond-earrings-design\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">modern diamond earrings design</span></a>, understanding purity will help you choose the perfect piece with confidence.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_ktAhRp": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Understanding_Diamond_Purity_16_9.png",
            "text": "<h2>Understanding Diamond Purity</h2><p>Diamond purity refers to how flawless and natural a diamond is, both inside and out. The fewer inclusions (internal marks) and blemishes (external imperfections), the purer the diamond.</p><p>Purity is often assessed based on the 4Cs:</p><ul><li>Cut – how well a diamond reflects light.<br/></li><li>Color – the degree to which it is colorless.<br/></li><li>Clarity – the presence of inclusions or blemishes.<br/></li><li>Carat – the diamond’s weight.<br/></li></ul><p>Even lab-grown diamonds, like those at Lucira Jewelry, are graded on the same scale and certified by IGI (International Gemological Institute) to guarantee purity and brilliance.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "column",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "adaptive",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "0-30-carat-segmented-diamond-mens-classic-ring",
              "0-30-cts-elegant-solitaire-diamond-ring"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Jc4E4r": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "How to Check Diamond Purity at Home",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>How to Check Diamond Purity at Home</h2><p>If you’re wondering how to check diamond purity at home, there are several quick and easy methods you can try without needing professional tools.</p>",
            "custom_id": "how",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_9LGxTw": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1. The Fog Test",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>1. The Fog Test</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_F9QPHC": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image Fog Test ",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/1._The_Fog_Test_V2.png",
            "text": "<p>Hold your diamond in front of your mouth and breathe on it, just as you would to fog a mirror. A real diamond disperses heat instantly, so the fog will disappear almost immediately. If the fog lingers for a few seconds, the stone is likely not pure or real.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_nTBBAL": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "2. The Water Test",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>2. The Water Test</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_AaUVCQ": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image Water Test",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/2._The_Water_Test.png",
            "text": "<p>Fill a glass with water and gently drop the diamond into it. Real diamonds are dense and will sink to the bottom, while fake ones often float. This is a simple yet effective way to test the purity of a diamond at home.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "0-252ct-half-eternity-prong-diamond-band",
              "0-30-cts-elegant-solitaire-diamond-ring"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_GiQ9B7": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "3. The Scratch Test",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>3. The Scratch Test</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_H8Xjm8": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image Scratch Test",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/3._The_Scratch_Test.png",
            "text": "<p>Diamonds are one of the hardest materials on Earth. Try gently scratching a piece of glass or ceramic plate with your stone. A genuine diamond will leave a mark on the glass but won’t be damaged itself. Be cautious with this test, as you don’t want to harm your jewelry.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Q6qRXX": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "4. The UV Light Test",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>4. The UV Light Test</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_xM6qFf": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image UV Light Test",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/4._The_UV_Light_Test.png",
            "text": "<p>Under ultraviolet light, many real diamonds emit a faint blue glow due to natural fluorescence. However, not all diamonds react the same way some may not fluoresce at all. This doesn’t mean they’re impure, but it’s another helpful clue in your home purity check.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": false,
            "products": []
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AahmV6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "5. The Sparkle Test",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>5. The Sparkle Test</h2>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_EN6aVa": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image Sparkle Test",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/5._The_Sparkle_Test.png",
            "text": "<p>Take your diamond into natural sunlight or under a bright lamp. Observe how it reflects light. Real diamonds produce both white and rainbow flashes of light—a captivating brilliance that synthetic stones rarely match. This sparkle can be seen beautifully in Lucira’s<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/rose-gold-diamond-necklace\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">rose gold diamond necklace</span></a> collection, where each piece is crafted for unmatched luminosity.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "row",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium",
            "show_products": true,
            "products": [
              "classic-lily-cut-diamond-pendant-necklace",
              "emerald-cut-diamond-bezel-set-earrings"
            ]
          }
        },
        "rich_text_6WCWXy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Professional Methods to Check Diamond Purity",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Professional Methods to Check Diamond Purity</h2><p>While home tests are useful, professional verification provides complete assurance.</p><h3>Thermal Conductivity Test</h3><p>Gemologists use a diamond tester pen that measures how fast heat moves through the stone. Real diamonds conduct heat quickly, confirming authenticity.</p><h3>Refractive Index Test</h3><p>This test checks how light bends inside the diamond. Real diamonds have a unique refractive index that sets them apart from imitations.</p><h3>Certification Check</h3><p>Always ask for an IGI or GIA certificate, which confirms the stone’s origin, clarity, and authenticity. Every Lucira diamond, from<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/lab-grown-diamond-studs\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">lab grown diamond studs</span></a> to engagement rings, comes with certification that guarantees purity and peace of mind.</p>",
            "custom_id": "professional",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_RAnXdT": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Certification_Check_3d30e284-8254-4054-9936-5888b99247db.png"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_rQKzCe": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Common Myths About Diamond Purity",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Common Myths About Diamond Purity</h2><h3>Myth 1: Lab-grown diamonds aren’t real.</h3><p>False. Lab-grown diamonds have the same chemical and physical properties as mined ones they’re just created in a lab environment.</p><h3>Myth 2: Only expensive diamonds are pure.</h3><p>Not true. Purity depends on the 4Cs, not just price. With brands like Lucira, you can find pure, certified diamonds at every budget.</p><h3>Myth 3: Home tests are always accurate.</h3><p>Home tests offer useful clues but are not definitive. Always verify with certified documents for complete assurance.</p>",
            "custom_id": "common",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_hPT9LP": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/The_Purity_Advantage_of_Lab-Grown_Diamonds.png",
            "text": "<h2>The Purity Advantage of Lab-Grown Diamonds</h2><p>One of the biggest advantages of lab-grown diamonds is consistency in purity. Created under controlled conditions using advanced CVD and HPHT technology, these diamonds exhibit minimal inclusions and superior clarity compared to many mined diamonds. <br/><br/>Lucira Jewelry’s lab-grown diamonds combine luxury with responsibility no mining, no conflict, just pure brilliance. Each piece reflects exceptional craftsmanship and ethical values that resonate with modern buyers.</p>",
            "layout_direction": "column",
            "reverse_layout": false,
